{
  "texts": [
    "Retrieval-Augmented Generation for Literature ReviewRetrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) combines the strengths of information retrieval and text generation to enhance the capability of LLMs in producing more accurate and relevant content [10,11].",
    "By retrieving information from a vast corpus of documents before generating responses, RAG enables LLMs to produce outputs that are not only contextually relevant, but also deeply grounded in the literature [12].",
    "This approach is particularly important to literature reviews, where the accuracy of information and the ability to draw from a broad range of sources are paramount [3,2].",
    "RAG's application in this context Literature reviews play a crucial role in scientific research, serving as foundational pillars that offer comprehensive insights into existing knowledge, identify gaps in the literature, and guide future research directions [1].",
    "The traditional manual process of conducting literature reviews is time-consuming and prone to human bias, leading to the exploration of automated systems to assist in this endeavor [2,3]."
  ]
}